postel@venera.isi.edu writes:
   I would have to have the DNS data base have the record:
		   POSTEL.MDR.CA.US	MX	MCI-MAIL.COM

Will this scale adequately?  Consider a really large entity of this
type - start at 100,000 users or so, and go up from there.
Maintaining yet another monster database strikes me as somehow
suboptimal.  Given that the entity (MCI or whatever) already has to
maintain the accounts database for all those users, perhaps that could
be mechanically edited into a nameserver database without much
problem; but still, account creation/destruction happens _all_ the
time - the database would be constantly changing.

yes/no/maybe?,
--Karl

